<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="45" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[264,1323,1151,1902]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">
DIAGNOSIS. This species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1822" box="[636,738,1151,1176]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Drapetis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[636,738,1151,1176]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Drapetis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished by its wing venation with R 
<subScript attach="right" box="[1292,1323,1163,1180]" fontSize="7" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">4+5</subScript>
slightly sinuous and strongly divergent from M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[846,877,1206,1223]" fontSize="7" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">1+2</subScript>
, as well as the apparent absence of ommatrichia and characteristic squamiform setae on male abdominal tergite 4 and 5 (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[264,368,1305,1329]" captionTargetBox="[265,1322,406,1262]" captionTargetId="figure-216@9.[265,1322,406,1281]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. Drapetis dissentis sp. nov. A. habitus. B. male thorax, dorsal view. C. wing, Scale 0.5 mm. D. male genitalia and apex of preabdomen, right lateral view, Scale 0.25 mm. Abbreviations: hypand — hypandrium; lt cerc — left cercus; rt cerc — right cercus; rt epand lam — right epandrial lamella; rt sur — right surstylus. (specimen B­8414­30)." pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="47" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[264,1323,1151,1902]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">
DESCRIPTION. Male (
<figureCitation box="[597,694,1316,1342]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[264,368,1305,1329]" captionTargetBox="[265,1322,406,1262]" captionTargetId="figure-216@9.[265,1322,406,1281]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. Drapetis dissentis sp. nov. A. habitus. B. male thorax, dorsal view. C. wing, Scale 0.5 mm. D. male genitalia and apex of preabdomen, right lateral view, Scale 0.25 mm. Abbreviations: hypand — hypandrium; lt cerc — left cercus; rt cerc — right cercus; rt epand lam — right epandrial lamella; rt sur — right surstylus. (specimen B­8414­30)." pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Length 
<quantity box="[809,919,1316,1342]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.64" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" unit="mm" value="1.64">1.64 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis box="[933,996,1316,1341]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Head</emphasis>
. Ground colour dark. Eyes apparently lacking ommatrichia (pubescence); narrowly separated below antennae; facets not noticeably enlarged below antennae. Frons with sides divergent; narrow just above antennae and slightly wider on vertex than width of ocellar triangle. Two pairs of ocellar bristles; anterior pair convergent, inserted between median and posterior ocelli and broadly separated; posterior pair inserted between posterior ocelli. Two pairs of convergent vertical bristles. Antennae arising slightly above middle of head; scape small, shorter than half length of pedicel; pedicel globose, two­thirds as long as postpedicel, lacking long ventral preapical bristle; postpedicel short­conical, with terminal arista­like style shorter than scutum; antennal segments concolorous (dark brown). Palpus ovate with several long, apical setulae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[264,1323,1151,1902]" lastBlockId="9.[264,1323,284,350]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="46" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis box="[312,396,1756,1781]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Thorax</emphasis>
. (
<figureCitation box="[421,511,1756,1782]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[264,368,1305,1329]" captionTargetBox="[265,1322,406,1262]" captionTargetId="figure-216@9.[265,1322,406,1281]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. Drapetis dissentis sp. nov. A. habitus. B. male thorax, dorsal view. C. wing, Scale 0.5 mm. D. male genitalia and apex of preabdomen, right lateral view, Scale 0.25 mm. Abbreviations: hypand — hypandrium; lt cerc — left cercus; rt cerc — right cercus; rt epand lam — right epandrial lamella; rt sur — right surstylus. (specimen B­8414­30)." pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
) Ground colour dark. Scutum entirely clothed in dense microtrichia, scutellum lacking microtrichia. Postpronotal lobe and bristles absent; 2 pairs of prescutellar acr; 1–2 npl; 1 pair of prescutellar dc; spal not clearly differentiated; 1 pal; 1 subapical pair of sctl, less than one­half length of apical sctl; 1 apical pair of sctl long and conver­ gent. Scutum appears entirely shiny, lacking tomentum; scutellum perhaps with tomentum on at least anterior half.
</paragraph>
<caption pageId="9" pageNumber="46" startId="9.[264,368,1305,1329]" targetBox="[265,1322,406,1262]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph blockId="9.[264,1323,1305,1432]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,395,1305,1329]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">FIGURE 3.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Solórzano Kraemer &amp; Sinclair &amp; Cumming, 2005" authorityName="Solórzano Kraemer &amp; Sinclair &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="2005" box="[402,595,1306,1329]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Drapetis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dissentis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[402,595,1306,1329]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Drapetis dissentis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[602,684,1305,1329]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[691,710,1305,1329]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">A</emphasis>
. habitus. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[815,833,1305,1329]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">B</emphasis>
. male thorax, dorsal view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1124,1143,1305,1329]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">C</emphasis>
. wing, Scale 0.5 mm. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[320,339,1340,1364]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">D</emphasis>
. male genitalia and apex of preabdomen, right lateral view, Scale 0.25 mm. Abbreviations: hypand — hypandrium; lt cerc — left cercus; rt cerc — right cercus; rt epand lam — right epandrial lamella; rt sur — right surstylus. (specimen B­8414­30).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="9.[264,1323,1484,1881]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis box="[312,372,1484,1509]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Wing</emphasis>
. (
<figureCitation box="[399,492,1484,1510]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[264,368,1305,1329]" captionTargetBox="[265,1322,406,1262]" captionTargetId="figure-216@9.[265,1322,406,1281]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. Drapetis dissentis sp. nov. A. habitus. B. male thorax, dorsal view. C. wing, Scale 0.5 mm. D. male genitalia and apex of preabdomen, right lateral view, Scale 0.25 mm. Abbreviations: hypand — hypandrium; lt cerc — left cercus; rt cerc — right cercus; rt epand lam — right epandrial lamella; rt sur — right surstylus. (specimen B­8414­30)." pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
) Length 
<quantity box="[607,704,1484,1510]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
. Broad with blunt­tip; hyaline; microtrichia evenly distributed; costal setulae well developed; Rs about one­half length of cell bm; R 
<subScript attach="right" box="[1292,1323,1537,1554]" fontSize="7" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">2+3</subScript>
strongly arched, extending to beyond mid­length of wing; R slightly sinuous, divergent from M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[355,385,1625,1642]" fontSize="7" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">1+2</subScript>
; cell br much shorter than cell bm; crossvein bm­cu nearly transverse. Knob of halter dark.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[264,1323,1484,1881]" box="[973,1004,1582,1599]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">
<subScript attach="left" box="[973,1004,1582,1599]" fontSize="7" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">4+5</subScript>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[264,1323,1484,1881]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis box="[312,367,1695,1720]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Legs</emphasis>
. Fore and mid femora moderately thickened. Mid femur with 1 outstanding preapical anterior bristle; mid tibia somewhat arched; first tarsomere with biserial ventral row of short bristles, slightly shorter than width of segment. Hind femur slightly bent near base, with row of short anteroventral bristles longer near apex. Hind tibia slightly arched with posteroventral row of short bristles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[264,1323,284,790]" pageId="10" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis box="[312,422,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="47">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Segments uniformly telescopic, without distinctive flattened hook­like squamiform setae on tergite 4 and 5. Terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[851,946,324,350]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[264,368,1305,1329]" captionTargetBox="[265,1322,406,1262]" captionTargetId="figure-216@9.[265,1322,406,1281]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. Drapetis dissentis sp. nov. A. habitus. B. male thorax, dorsal view. C. wing, Scale 0.5 mm. D. male genitalia and apex of preabdomen, right lateral view, Scale 0.25 mm. Abbreviations: hypand — hypandrium; lt cerc — left cercus; rt cerc — right cercus; rt epand lam — right epandrial lamella; rt sur — right surstylus. (specimen B­8414­30)." pageId="10" pageNumber="47">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
): Right surstylus as long as terminalia, with stout inner marginal bristles. Right cercus slender, slightly tapered. Left cercus broad, digitiform, only slightly tapered to rounded apex. Hypandrium broad and truncate apically.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
