<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="47" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[264,1323,284,790]" pageId="10" pageNumber="47">
REMARKS. The inclusion was found together with a specimen of 
<taxonomicName box="[1138,1319,604,630]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Cecidomyiidae</taxonomicName>
. Extant species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1822" box="[477,580,644,669]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Drapetis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[477,580,644,669]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="47">Drapetis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are found in a wide variety of habitats on vegetation and tree trunks, in rodent burrows, and in ant nests (
<bibRefCitation author="Rogers, E." box="[772,927,684,710]" pageId="10" pageNumber="47" pagination="431 - 452" refId="ref6683" refString="Rogers, E. (1983) The Neotropical species of Drapetis Meigen (Diptera: Empididae). Systematic Entomology, 8, 431 - 452." type="journal article" year="1983">Rogers 1983</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="47" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[264,1323,284,790]" pageId="10" pageNumber="47">
ETYMOLOGY. From the Latin, 
<emphasis box="[710,744,724,749]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="47">dis</emphasis>
(without) and 
<emphasis box="[925,992,724,749]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="47">sentis</emphasis>
(thorn), in reference to the lack of squamiform setae on male abdominal tergite 4 and 5.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
